column2: "Hello, survivor," Fat Joe said. \n" It's always good to see new faces in this apocalyptic chaos. " \n" I'm Fat Joe, and if you need supplies, or just want to make a friend, you've come to the right person. Just don't bring those brainless guys and we can have a good chat. "
column3: “你好，幸存者。”肥乔说道。\n“在这末日的混乱中看到新面孔总是一件好事。”\n“我是肥乔，如果你需要补给，或者只是想要交个朋友，你都找对人了。只要别带来那些没脑子的家伙，我们就能好好聊聊。”

column2: "Hello." \n" I'm Gavin and I take over the business of the camp. " \n" The things you have on hand can be exchanged, and the money is paid and delivered. It's that simple. "
column3: “你好。”\n“我是加文，营地的交易由我接手。”\n“你手头里的东西可以拿来交换，一手交钱一手交货，就这么简单。”

column2: "Maybe the seat belt saved you and prevented you from being thrown out of the cabin. As for why the accident occurred, our military has found out the general cause. So there is no need to know anything from you. If you feel that your body is not healthy If there is any abnormality, you can be discharged to the town center."
column3: “可能是安全带救了你，没让你被甩出机舱外，至于为什么会发生事故，我们的军方已经查明了大致原因了。所以不需要从你这了解什么。如果你感觉身体没多大异样的话，你就可以出院到镇中心了。”

column2: "Oh, remember to take your things when you leave the hospital. We found them next to you." He added.
column3: “哦，出院记得拿上你的东西，我们在你旁边发现的。”他补充到。

column2: "Hey, you're awake. You're so lucky. You're the only one who survived the entire plane." He said, "When our army arrived at the scene, they found dead people everywhere beside the helicopter, including the pilot. During cabin inspection, it was discovered that you were in a seat."
column3: “嘿，你醒了。你可真是幸运，整个飞机就你一个人活了下来。”他说道，“我们军队到达现场的时候，发现直升机的旁边横七竖八的到处都是死人，甚至还有飞行员，在机舱检查时，就发现你在一个座位上。”

column2: "We have to find a new shelter," the pilot said to you through the radio. "I don't know what happened to our previous shelter. A large-scale infection suddenly broke out. I thought we were all immune..."

column2: "Are you a survivor on the plane?" the girl said with a smile. She took a photo of you with a camera, and then picked up a pen and asked for your name.

column2:
"Life is getting harder and harder these days. Food is scarce. I heard that the crazy people in District 13 have started to eat each other." 
 Fat Joe stopped what he was doing and moved closer to you. 
" But I heard there's a cannery nearby that might still have some in stock. " 
" I tried going in once, but there were more zombies than there were rats in the whole city, and, the smell..." He wrinkled his nose. 
" If we can get hold of those cans, we'll be able to hold on for a while at least. But I gotta tell you, it's not an easy job. Those zombies, they... they are not like those wanderers on the street, and it is rare for them to stink for a few days. " 
" Negan once brought a large group of people there, but they all retreated after not knowing what they encountered. "
column3:
“这日子过得越来越艰难了，食物稀少，听说十三区那帮疯子已经开始互啃了。”
  肥乔停下手中的活计，向你靠近了一些。
“但我听说附近有个罐头加工厂，可能还有存货。”
“我试过一次进去，但那里的僵尸比这整个城市的老鼠还要多，而且，那味道…” 他皱起了鼻子。
“如果我们能搞到那些罐头，至少能撑一阵子。但我得告诉你，那不是件容易的活。那些丧尸，他们…他们不像街上的那些游荡者，被他们沾上臭几天都算少的。”
“尼根曾拉一大帮人过去一次，不知道他们遇到了什么东西，后面都撤回来了。”
